JIRA does not support Opera Browser.  However, the Javascript that is generated by the issue collector plugin is not working if the user is using Opera while accessing the page which contains the script. 

The Issue Collector plugin should be generated to be browser independent, so that any user who wants to leave a feedback can do so in any browser.  

One customer has a suggestion to fix this case:
{noformat}
Issue was debugged and it's related to the CSS embedded in JavaScript. This CSS embedded in JavaScript does contain following rules:{code}-webkit-transform-origin:top left;
-webkit-transform: rotate(90deg);
-moz-transform: rotate(90deg);
-moz-transform-origin:top left;
-ms-transform: rotate(90deg);
-ms-transform-origin:top left;{code}

As you can see, only Webkit (webkit), Gecko (moz) and Trident (ms) are supported. The fix is extremely trivial and requires just adding two new rules:{code}-o-transform: rotate(90deg);
-o-transform-origin:top left;{code}
They will handle Opera (o prefix).
---
{noformat}

