Referring to the documentation of [Advanced Searching|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Advanced+Searching], you can *only* use the operator *WAS*, *WAS IN*, *WAS NOT IN*, *WAS NOT*, and *CHANGED* specifically for _some_ *System Fields* only:
{quote} 
(Note: This operator can be used with the Assignee, Fix Version, Priority, Reporter, Resolution and Status fields only.)
{quote}

It will be useful if it can be used for *Custom Field* values and _all_ System Fields as well. An example of the proposed improvement would be something like:
{code}
project = "ABC" and cf[10286] = "Cat 1" and cf[10286] WAS "Cat 2"
{code}

